The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 7: Tata Steel has bought an additional stake in New Millennium Capital Corp for about Rs 89.25 crore, increasing its shareholding in the Canadian mining company to 27.4 per cent. Tata Steels subsidiary Tata Steel Global Minerals Holdings bought 14.2 million common shares in the mining entity for 1.40 Canadian dollar apiece, amounting to a total of 20 million Canadian dollars.                            
	 New Delhi, June 7: Seven public sector banks may get additional capital from the government soon, financial services secretary R. Gopalan said. The banking division has sought the approval of finance minister Pranab Mukherjee for the purpose.                             
	 Calcutta, June 7: Kishore Chhabria-promoted Allied Blenders amp; Distillers plans to offload 5-10 per cent stake to private equity funds, followed by its maiden IPO in the middle of next year.                            
	 Chandigarh, June 7: Asim Dasgupta, chairman of the empowered committee of state finance ministers, today said the panel expected the constitutional amendment bill for the introduction of the Goods and Services Tax to be tabled in the monsoon session of Parliament.                             
	 New Delhi, June 7: Honda Siel Cars India has launched a version of its sedan Civic, priced between Rs 12.20 lakh and Rs 13.81 lakh. The new Civic comes in three variants and is fitted with a 1.8 litre i-VTEC engine.                            
	 New Delhi, June 7: The government will take up six fresh requests for setting up SEZs tomorrow. The Board of Approval on SEZs will also consider framing rules to allow migration of units from one zone to another.                             
	 New Delhi, June 7: Former banker Yogesh Agarwal today took over as the interim chairman of the Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority.                                                                                                                          
